{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Identifiable/ID-swift.associatedtype"],"title":"Specifying the Associated Type","anchor":"Specifying-the-Associated-Type"},{"title":"Specifying the Identified Item","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Identifiable/id-8t2ws"],"anchor":"Specifying-the-Identified-Item"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Identifiable","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A class of types whose instances hold the value of an entity with stable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identity."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Equatable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Comparable"],"title":"Equality and Ordering","anchor":"Equality-and-Ordering"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Identifiable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Identifiable/ID-swift.associatedtype","preciseIdentifier":"s:s12IdentifiableP2IDQa","text":"ID","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Identifiable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol to provide a stable notion of identity to a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"class or value type. For example, you could define a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"User"},{"text":" type with an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"property that is stable across your app and your app’s database storage."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"You could use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" property to identify a particular user even if other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data fields change, such as the user’s name."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Identifiable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" leaves the duration and scope of the identity unspecified.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Identities can have any of the following characteristics:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Guaranteed always unique, like UUIDs."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Persistently unique per environment, like database record keys.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unique for the lifetime of a process, like global incrementing integers."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unique for the lifetime of an object, like object identifiers."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unique within the current collection, like collection indices."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s up to both the conformer and the receiver of the protocol to document"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the nature of the identity."}]},{"anchor":"Conforming-to-the-Identifiable-Protocol","level":1,"type":"heading","text":"Conforming to the Identifiable Protocol"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Identifiable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a default implementation for class types (using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ObjectIdentifier"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is only guaranteed to remain unique for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{